description.plain: Tenacious D is an American comedy rock duo that was formed in Los Angeles, California in 1994. Composed of lead vocalist and guitarist Jack Black and lead guitarist and vocalist Kyle Gass, the band has released four albums – Tenacious D  (2001), The Pick of Destiny (2006, along with a movie of the same name), Rize of the Fenix  (2012), and Post-Apocalypto (2018), which was released one song at a time in an animated show on Youtube. Tenacious D’s studio releases, and (as of 2006) its live performances, feature a full band lineup, including such musicians as guitarist John Konesky and bassist John Spiker. Drummer Dave Grohl (Foo Fighters, Nirvana) played on every studio release.

“Tribute” was released as the lead single off their self-titled debut album. The song plays out as a tribute to the actual best song in the world that the D have forgotten what sounded like. It is one of, if not the most recognizable song by Tenacious D.

In an interview with JimmyO, Kyle and Jack said that the inspiration from the song came after Jack played Metallica’s “One“ for Kyle. Jack: “I turned it on… turned Kyle onto it and I said, “I think they’re the best band in the world. Metallica. And I think this song is the best song in the world.” And then Kyle agreed after he listened to it thrice. At first he said nay. Then he said perhaps. And then he said yeah.”
This then lead to a failed attempt to write an even better song themselves which became the song Tribute, after a discussion of the meaninglessness of labeling any song “the best” since they say it is impossible to reach musical perfection.

There are lots of claims that the song is a tribute to “Stairway to Heaven,” since they sound alike. Both songs are played in A minor and also their chord progressions are quite similar. They also play the intro and interludes of Stairway to Heaven in many live versions and the TV series version. However, the lyrics make clear that “Tribute” sounds nothing like the song they came up with to please the demon.

Some people think that Tribute is a tribute to the song “Beelzeboss (The Final Showdown),” which they played in the rock-off challenge between Satan and Tenacious D in their movie “Tenacious D in The Pick of Destiny.” After defeating Satan, Jack and Kyle recall the incident once more, describing it as, “the greatest song in the world”. Unfortunately, they are unable to remember how it went. In the movie it was made to look like “Tribute” was to Beelzeboss on purpose. However, “Tribute” was their first song and thus was written four years before the movie was made.

It tells the story of the young JB, who wants to become a rockstar, but because he comes from an extremely religious family, his father forbids him to listen to heavy music, thinking it comes from the Devil, therefore should not be played in their house. Later Dio tells him to escape and go to Hollywood, which he does.

body.plain: Tenacious D is an American comedy rock duo that was formed in Los Angeles, California in 1994. Composed of lead vocalist and guitarist Jack Black and lead guitarist and vocalist Kyle Gass, the band has released four albums – Tenacious D  (2001), The Pick of Destiny (2006, along with a movie of the same name), Rize of the Fenix  (2012), and Post-Apocalypto (2018), which was released one song at a time in an animated show on Youtube. Tenacious D’s studio releases, and (as of 2006) its live performances, feature a full band lineup, including such musicians as guitarist John Konesky and bassist John Spiker. Drummer Dave Grohl (Foo Fighters, Nirvana) played on every studio release.
